  body
        
    .site
      a.logo(href='/')
      .scroll_container
        .grid_container
          .grid_item.grid_item_large(tabindex='1', data-video-src='some source', )
            .titel
              | the <verystrong>Virtual Mixer Project</verystrong><br>
              | Lets try videomixing in javascript v0.0.1
            .content
              | 
              | <p> This is the <verystrong>DEMOS SECTION</verystrong> </p>
              | <p> <a href="/"> <<-- Back to the home page </a>
              | <br>
              | <br>
              | To help you on your way, and to show of the possibilities of the virtual mixer this demo page 
              | was added to the site. Some of these are tested and solid features of the project, others
              | are feeble technical demos or early prototypes.
              | Where possible code examples and references were added.
              | <br>
              | </p>                
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://github.com/Sense-Studios/VirtualMixerProject" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/91/Octicons-mark-github.svg"/> Github Repository</a> | 
              | <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jYwPJXsD-mc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c9/YouTube_play_buttom_dark_icon_%282013-2017%29.svg"/> Youtube</a> | 
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>

          .grid_item(tabindex="2", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/tapped_beat.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>Tapped BPM</verystrong>            
            .content
              | Easy interface for tapped bpm. Tap along with any song pressing ENTER this Addon will give you your BPM back. Integrates easily with the mixer. 
              | 
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://codepen.io/xangadix/pen/drqzPr" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c0/Feather-logos-codepen.svg"/> Codepen</a>               
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Addon_BPM.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>

          .grid_item(tabindex="2", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/analysis.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>BPM DETECTION</verystrong>            
            .content
              | Yes, realtime bpm detection! Tries and detects the BPM of any mp3 or shoutcast stream.
              | Demo with a number of songs and metronomes.
              | 
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://codepen.io/xangadix/pen/VRGzdY" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c0/Feather-logos-codepen.svg"/> Codepen</a>               
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Addon_AudioAnalysis.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>


          .grid_item(tabindex="2", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/webcam.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>Webcam</verystrong>            
            .content
              | A wrapper around GetUserMedia(). Requires https. Should give you easy access to a Webcam as a source.
              | 
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://codepen.io/xangadix/pen/moLayR" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c0/Feather-logos-codepen.svg"/> Codepen</a>               
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Source_WebcamSource.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>

          .grid_item(tabindex="2", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/effects.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>effects and blendmodes</verystrong>            
            .content
              | A growing range of color-, distortion and feedback effects. Here is a small demo showing off all effects and mixer blendmodes!
              | 
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://codepen.io/xangadix/pen/eXLGwJ" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c0/Feather-logos-codepen.svg"/> Codepen</a>               
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Effect.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>

          .grid_item(tabindex="3", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/keyboard.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>Keyboard</verystrong>            
            .content
              | I've been using gamepads for live mixing since 2004. Of course it needed to be in here.              
              | <br>
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://codepen.io/xangadix/pen/NJzxNy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c0/Feather-logos-codepen.svg"/> Codepen </a>               
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Controller_KeyboardController.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>


          .grid_item(tabindex="4", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/gamepad.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>Gamepad</verystrong>            
            .content
              | I've been using gamepads for live mixing since 2004. Of course it needed to be in here.       
              | Check               
              | <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3FbJK2uQfb8" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              |  <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c9/YouTube_play_buttom_dark_icon_%282013-2017%29.svg"/>
              |  this liverecording
              | </a>
              | which is a recreation, mostly, of the original mixer I used in 
              | VJO in 2004, but now in Javascript. And with vastly more framerate and resolution.
              | <br>
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://codepen.io/xangadix/pen/gEzZgx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c0/Feather-logos-codepen.svg"/> Codepen</a>               
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Controller_GamePadController.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>

          .grid_item(tabindex="5", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/midi.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>MIDI</verystrong>            
            .content
              | Complete wrapper around MIDI(). Includes sending back of signals for blinking lights and such. Tested on Akai APC mini and Akai MPK mini              
              | <p class="hidden">
              | <strong>CHECK OUT</strong> this  
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/mixer/demos" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Midi Piano for Akai MPK</a>              
              | Utilizing Appreggioo              
              |  - AND check the 
              | <a href="https://youtu.be/lxDyoGKMsRY?t=327"target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> 
              |  <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c9/YouTube_play_buttom_dark_icon_%282013-2017%29.svg"/>
              |  Video               
              | </a>               
              | </p>
              | <br>
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://codepen.io/xangadix/pen/BbVogR" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c0/Feather-logos-codepen.svg"/>Codepen</a>
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Controller_MidiController.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/>Documentation</a>

          .grid_item(tabindex="6", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/sockets.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>Sockets</verystrong>            
            .content
              | Working with Sockets can be confusing. So here is a wrapper for sockets.io that
              | allows you to easily connect different browsers together. It tries to assign a pin code, not unlike a Chromecast.
              | when connected events can easily be sent. Be it from a mobile phone or any other device.
              | <br>
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/mixer/demo_socket_client" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Client</a> |
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/controllers/demo_socketcontroller_remote" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Remote</a>
              | <br>
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/docs/reference/Controller_SocketController.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> <img class="text-icon" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/99/Unofficial_JavaScript_logo_2.svg"/> Documentation</a>


          .grid_item(tabindex="7", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/trackeditor.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>Sequencer</verystrong>            
            .content
              | Still an early techdemo. Tracker-like interface to configure mixer controls.
              | <br>
              | <br>
              | <hr>              
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/editors/TrackEditor">techdemo</a>

          .grid_item(tabindex="8", data-video-src="/video/placeholder.mp4")
            img.item_image(src="/images/vmp_demo/clock.png")
            .titel
              | <verystrong>Clicktrack</verystrong>                        
            .content
              | Early demo of a clicktrack script, that lets you script a set of mixers and effects.
              | now works through Google Spreadsheets.
              | <br>
              | <br>
              | <hr>
              | <a href="https://virtualmixproject.com/mixer/clicktrack">techdemo</a>

